BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Additional CSS classes for the accordion container.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandedItemId
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            ID of the expanded item.
            Do not use constant value as it reverts the accordion to that item on every roundtrip. Use <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxAccordion.InitialExpandedItemId" /> to set the initial state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StayOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to <c>true</c> to make accordion items stay open when another item is opened.
            Default is <c>false</c>, openning another item collapses current item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InitialExpandedItemId
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            ID of the item you want to expand at the very beginning (overwrites <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxAccordion.ExpandedItemId" /> if set).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            You can set an explicit <c>false</c> constant to disable (override) the spinner automation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SingleClickProtection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set <c>false</c> if you want to allow multiple <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxButton.OnClick" /> handlers in parallel. Default is <c>true</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdditionalAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Additional attributes to be splatted onto an underlying <c><button></c> element.
            </summary>

<summary>
            Display controls to switch between slides.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Indicators
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Display indicators showing which slide is active. Can also be used to switch between slides.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dark
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Show controls, captions, etc. to dark colors.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Crossfade
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Animate slides with a fade transition instead of slide.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Interval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Delay for automatically switching slides. Default is <c>3000 ms</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TouchSwiping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable swiping left/right on touchscreen devices to move between slides.
            Default is <c>true</c> (enabled).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnSlide
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Is fired when the current slide is changed (at the very start of the sliding transition).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnSlid
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Is fired when the current slide is changed (once the transition is completed).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Carousel ride (autoplay) behavior. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.CarouselRide.Carousel" /> (autoplays the carousel on load).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Pause
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Carousel pause behavior. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.CarouselPause.Hover" /> (carousel will stop sliding on hover).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            Default is <c>null</c> (unlimited).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
Hint to browsers as to the type of virtual keyboard configuration to use when editing.
If not set (neither with nor , i.e. null), the will be used for equal to 0. We cannot set for greater that 0 as the users with keyboard locale not matching the application locale won't be able to enter decimal point (is , in some locales and . in others).
Feel free to set the InputMode on your own as needed.

TagHelpers.Name: Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxGrid<TItem>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Grid to display tabular data from data source. Includes support for client-side and server-side paging & sorting (or virtualized scrolling as needed).
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TItem">Type of row data item.</typeparam>

BoundAttributes.Name: TItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TItem for the Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxGrid<TItem> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: Settings
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set of settings to be applied to the component instance (overrides <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxGrid.Defaults" />, overriden by individual parameters).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataProvider
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
Data provider for items to render.
The provider should always return instance of , null is not allowed.

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectionEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether single data item selection is enabled. 
            Selection is performed by click on the item row.
            Can be combined with multiselection.
            Default is <c>true</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MultiSelectionEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether multi data items selection is enabled. 
            Selection is performed by checkboxes in the first column.
            Can be combined with (single) selection.
            Default is <c>false</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Columns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Columns template.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ContextMenu
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Context menu template.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadingDataTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Template to render when "first" data are loading.
            This template is not used when loading data for sorting or paging operations.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EmptyDataTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Template to render when there is empty Data (but not <c>null</c>).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedDataItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Selected data item.
            Intended for data binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedDataItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event fires when selected data item changes.
            Intended for data binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedDataItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Selected data items.
            Intended for data binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedDataItemsChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event fires when selected data items changes.
            Intended for data binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ContentNavigationMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Strategy how data are displayed in the grid (and loaded to the grid).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PageSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Page size for <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.GridContentNavigationMode.Pagination" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowFooterWhenEmptyData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether to render footer when data are empty.
            Default is <c>false</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentUserState
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Current grid state (page, sorting).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentUserStateChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event fires when grid state is changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InProgress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates when the grid should be displayed as "in progress".
            When not set (<c>null</c>), grid progress is automatically tracked when retrieving data by data provider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TableContainerCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to render with <c>div</c> element wrapping the main <c>table</c> (<see cref="T:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxPager" /> is not wrapped in this <c>div</c> element).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TableCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to render with main <c>table</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderRowCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to render with header <c>tr</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemRowCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to render with data <c>tr</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemRowHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Height of the item row used for infinite scroll calculations.
            Default value is <c>41px</c> (row-height of regular table-row within Bootstrap 5 default theme).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemRowCssClassSelector
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns custom CSS class to render with data <c>tr</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterRowCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to render with footer <c>tr</c> element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PagerCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom CSS class to add to the pager.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PlaceholdersRowCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Number of rows with placeholders to render.
            When value is zero, placeholders are not used.
            When <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxGrid`1.LoadingDataTemplate" /> is set, placeholder are not used.
            Default is <c>5</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverscanCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
Infinite scroll: Gets or sets a value that determines how many additional items will be rendered before and after the visible region. This help to reduce the frequency of rendering during scrolling. However, higher values mean that more elements will be present in the page.
Default is 50.

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

TagHelpers.Name: Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas
TagHelpers.Documentation: Bootstrap Offcanvas component (aka Drawer).

BoundAttributes.Name: Settings
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set of settings to be applied to the component instance (overrides <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.Defaults" />, overriden by individual parameters).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Text for the title in header.
            (Is rendered into <c><h5 class="offcanvas-title"></c> - in opposite to <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.HeaderTemplate" /> which is rendered directly into <c>offcanvas-header</c>).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Content for the header.
            (Is rendered directly into <c>offcanvas-header</c> - in opposite to <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.Title" /> which is rendered into <c><h5 class="offcanvas-title"></c>).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BodyTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Body content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Footer content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Placement of the offcanvas. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.OffcanvasPlacement.End" /> (right).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RenderMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Determines whether the content is always rendered or only if the offcanvas is open. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.OffcanvasRenderMode.OpenOnly" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Size of the offcanvas. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.OffcanvasSize.Regular" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCloseButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the modal shows close button in header.
            Default value is <c>true</c>.
            Use <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.CloseButtonIcon" /> to change shape of the button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseOnEscape
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the offcanvas closes when escape key is pressed.
            Default value is <c>true</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseButtonIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Close icon to be used in header.
            If set to <c>null</c>, Bootstrap default close-button will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BackdropEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether to apply a backdrop on body while offcanvas is open.
            Default value (from <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.Defaults" />) is <c>true</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollingEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether body (page) scrolling is allowed while offcanvas is open.
            Default value (from <see cref="P:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.HxOffcanvas.Defaults" />) is <c>false</c>.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Offcanvas additional CSS class. Added to root <c>div</c> (<c>.offcanvas</c>).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Additional header CSS class.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BodyCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Additional body CSS class.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterCssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Additional footer CSS class.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClosed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This event is fired when an offcanvas element has been hidden from the user (will wait for CSS transitions to complete).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnShown

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Placement of the offcanvas. Default is <see cref="F:Havit.Blazor.Components.Web.Bootstrap.OffcanvasPlacement.End" /> (right).

<summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseButtonIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            If set to <c>null</c>, Bootstrap default close-button will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BackdropEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollingEnabled

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxParallelUploads

Can be used in AuthorizeRouteView, Router and such components to process redirection to login page, error page or such.

Default is false.

             is authorized to see it.

            <remarks>

            <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator.GenerateTextBox(Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ViewContext,Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExplorer,System.String,System.Object,System.String,System.Object)" />.

            helper to call and the default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> value. A default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is not calculated
            if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is <c>checkbox</c>,

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test-property
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackTestClass" /> and <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackTestValue" />,
            and either <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHref" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.LinkTagHelper.FallbackHrefInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test-value

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.OptionTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <option> elements.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            This <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> works in conjunction with <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.SelectTagHelper" />. It reads elements
            content but does not modify that content. The only modification it makes is to add a <c>selected</c> attribute
            in some cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value for the <option> element.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Renders a partial view.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name or path of the partial view that is rendered to the response.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: for
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An expression to be evaluated against the current model. Cannot be used together with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.Model" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: model
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The model to pass into the partial view. Cannot be used together with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.For" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: optional
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When optional, executing the tag helper will no-op if the view cannot be located.
            Otherwise will throw stating the view could not be found.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: fallback-name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            View to lookup if the view specified by <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PartialTagHelper.Name" /> cannot be located.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: view-data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ViewDataDictionary" /> to pass into the partial view.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PersistComponentStateTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            A <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.TagHelper" /> that saves the state of Razor components rendered on the page up to that point.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: persist-mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.PersistComponentStateTagHelper.PersistenceMode" /> for the state to persist.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <script> elements that supports fallback src paths.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The tag helper won't process for cases with just the 'src' attribute.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Address of the external script to use.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to load.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from loading.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.SrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of a Script tag to fallback to in the case the primary one fails.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-suppress-fallback-integrity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Boolean value that determines if an integrity hash will be compared with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrc" /> value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-append-version
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value indicating if file version should be appended to src urls.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            A query string "v" with the encoded content of the file is added.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to fallback to in the case the
            primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from the fallback list, in
            the case the primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The script method defined in the primary script to use for the fallback test.
            </summary>

            attribute.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-validation-summary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.All" /> or <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.ModelOnly" />, appends a validation
            summary. Otherwise (<see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.None" />, the default), this tag helper does nothing.
            </summary>
            <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentException">
            Thrown if setter is called with an undefined <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper.ValidationSummary" /> value e.g.
            <c>(ValidationSummary)23</c>.
            </exception>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
